# Code Conventions

## Components

- Functional components + hooks ONLY (no class components)
- Props interface: `{ComponentName}Props`
- Named exports only (no default exports)
- Colocated tests: `ComponentName.test.tsx`

## TypeScript

- Strict mode — no `any`, no `@ts-ignore`
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for simple types
- Import types: `import type { X } from "..."`

## Files

- kebab-case for files: `element-utils.ts`
- PascalCase for components: `LayerUI.tsx`

## How to verify

1. Run `yarn test:code` (ESLint) — must pass with zero warnings; catches `any`, `@ts-ignore`, default exports
2. Run `grep -r "export default" packages/` — must return no results (named exports only)
3. Run `grep -rn "import {" packages/ | grep -v "import type"` — all type-only imports must use `import type`
4. Check that new `.tsx` files use `PascalCase` and new `.ts` utility files use `kebab-case` via `git diff --name-only HEAD`
